<s docid="LA072190-0055" num="6"> TV PLAGIARISM CHARGE</s>
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>

<s docid="LA072190-0055" num="7"> Re "It May Not Be Plagiarism, but It's a Rip-Off," Howard Rosenberg's July 11 column on KCAL Channel 9's unattributed use of the pictures and script of a CNN feature: Rosenberg quotes Channel 9's John Corcoran as saying he would be "highly offended to be called a plagiarist".</s>

<s docid="LA072190-0055" num="8"> Corcoran, if you're offended you should study that part of the definition of plagiarism that talks about putting your name on someone else's work.</s>
</P>
<P>

<s docid="LA072190-0055" num="9"> And shame on KCAL news director Bob Henry for calling it "a non-issue" because KCAL pays for CNN services.</s>

<s docid="LA072190-0055" num="10"> Perhaps Corcoran and Henry could explain how such a no-class position is any different from that of some airhead student who claims that he shouldn't get an F for buying a report from a term-paper mill and putting his own name on it as its author.</s>

<s docid="LA072190-0055" num="11"> Well, I guess if he did retype it himself.</s>

<s docid="LA072190-0055" num="12">. . .</s>
</P>
