<TEXT>
<P>

<s docid="LA110889-0155" num="9"> Humorist Art Buchwald will call several prominent Hollywood writers, including director-screenwriter Billy Wilder, as expert witnesses in his plagiarism lawsuit against Paramount Pictures Corp.</s>
</P>
<P>

<s docid="LA110889-0155" num="10"> In the $5-million suit, set for trial in state court next month, Buchwald contends that the Eddie Murphy movie "Coming to America" is similar to an idea called "King for a Day" that the columnist came up with in 1983.</s>
</P>
<P>

<s docid="LA110889-0155" num="11"> Both stories involve African princes who come to the United States and fall in love.</s>
</P>
<P>

<s docid="LA110889-0155" num="12"> The studio has denied the plagiarism allegations.</s>

<s docid="LA110889-0155" num="13"> Late last month, Los Angeles Superior Court Judge Harvey Schneider denied a motion by Paramount to dismiss the lawsuit.</s>
</P>
